# GraphCoding rules — this repo codes against its knowledge graph

- Before editing any file, run `graphcoding show <path>` and read its summary and
  incoming edges (blast radius). Do not edit files whose blast radius you have not seen.
- Before creating any file, run `graphcoding plan <path> -s "<one-line intent>"`
  with `-e IMPORTS:<dep>` edges. Do not create files that are not planned.
- Before deleting any file, run `graphcoding mark-delete <path>`. If it refuses
  (callers exist), rewire the callers first.
- Record dependencies static analysis cannot see (HTTP calls, queues, cron→table)
  with `graphcoding link <src> CALLS <dst>`.
- Before every commit, run `graphcoding sync --staged` and include
  `.graphcoding/graph.jsonl` in the commit. Never use `git commit --no-verify`.
- A task is done only when `graphcoding drift` prints `DRIFT=NONE` and
  `graphcoding status` shows no planned/to-be-deleted items from the task.
- If the graph disagrees with the code, fix the graph immediately
  (`graphcoding sync --files <path>`), never work around it.
